---
import Base from "@/layouts/Base.astro";
import {
  BRAND_NAME,
  SITE_URL,
  PARENT_ORG,
  PARENT_ORG_URL,
  GITHUB_REPO_URL,
} from "@/lib/config";
import { breadcrumbListSchema } from "@/lib/schema";

const canonical = `${SITE_URL}/about`;
const jsonLd = breadcrumbListSchema([
  { name: "Home", url: SITE_URL },
  { name: "About", url: canonical },
]);
---

<Base
  title={`About | ${BRAND_NAME}`}
  description="An independent monthly benchmark of every major AI humanizer. Operated transparently by WriteHuman."
  canonical={canonical}
  ogImage={`${SITE_URL}/og/about.png`}
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>
  <article
    class="max-w-3xl mx-auto py-16 px-6 text-[var(--color-text-primary)] [&_h1]:text-4xl [&_h1]:font-semibold [&_h1]:tracking-tight [&_h1]:mb-8 [&_h2]:text-2xl [&_h2]:font-semibold [&_h2]:tracking-tight [&_h2]:mt-12 [&_h2]:mb-4 [&_p]:mt-4 [&_p]:leading-relaxed [&_p]:text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] [&_ul]:mt-4 [&_ul]:space-y-2 [&_ul]:pl-6 [&_ul]:list-disc [&_ul]:text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] [&_a]:text-[var(--color-accent)] [&_a:hover]:underline [&_code]:font-mono [&_code]:text-[0.9em] [&_code]:px-1 [&_code]:py-0.5 [&_code]:rounded [&_code]:bg-[var(--color-surface)] [&_code]:border [&_code]:border-[var(--color-border)] [&_strong]:font-semibold [&_strong]:text-[var(--color-text-primary)]"
  >
    <h1>About HumanizerBench</h1>

    <p>
      <strong>HumanizerBench</strong> is an independent monthly benchmark of
      every major AI humanizer on the market. Each cycle, we run the same set
      of prompts through every tested humanizer, submit each humanized output
      to six commercial AI detectors, score the results with a published
      deterministic formula, and ship the raw data (inputs, outputs, detector
      responses, scoring script) alongside the leaderboard.
    </p>
    <p>
      The market for AI humanizers is noisy. Every vendor claims the highest
      bypass rate against the most detectors with the best meaning
      preservation. We exist to give that market one credible, auditable
      reference: the same inputs, the same detectors, the same scoring, every
      month. If we say a humanizer ranks third, you can download the cycle and
      reproduce the rank yourself. The longer version of <a href="/why"
        >why we built this</a
      > goes into more depth.
    </p>
    <p>
      We're operated by {PARENT_ORG}, which sells one of the humanizers on
      this leaderboard. We disclose that on every page and we hold WriteHuman
      to exactly the same methodology, scoring, and penalty rules as every
      other tested humanizer. Total transparency is the only credibility play
      that works when the operator is also a competitor.
    </p>

    <h2>Operator</h2>
    <p>
      HumanizerBench is operated by <a
        href={PARENT_ORG_URL}
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        target="_blank">{PARENT_ORG} ({PARENT_ORG_URL})</a
      >. {PARENT_ORG} builds an AI humanizer for writers, students, and
      marketing teams. Editorial control of the benchmark (what we test, how
      we score, what we publish) is independent of WriteHuman's commercial
      product team.
    </p>

    <h2>Anti-bias commitments</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        WriteHuman is tested using the same methodology and scoring as every
        other humanizer.
      </li>
      <li>The scoring script is public and deterministic.</li>
      <li>We do not adjust rankings outside the published methodology.</li>
      <li>We do not accept payment for placement.</li>
      <li>
        We do not exclude tools because they outperform WriteHuman, and we do
        not run private tests off the record.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      The full version of these commitments, and how to dispute, retest, or
      submit API access, is on the <a href="/fairness"
        >fairness &amp; corrections page</a
      >.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Press: <a href="mailto:press@humanizerbench.example"
          >press@humanizerbench.example</a
        >
      </li>
      <li>
        Partnerships: <a href="mailto:partnerships@humanizerbench.example"
          >partnerships@humanizerbench.example</a
        >
      </li>
      <li>
        Disputes &amp; corrections: <a
          href="mailto:disputes@humanizerbench.example"
          >disputes@humanizerbench.example</a
        > (see <a href="/fairness">fairness</a> for the full process)
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Open source</h2>
    <p>
      All inputs, outputs, detector responses, and the scoring script live in
      our public repository: <a
        href={GITHUB_REPO_URL}
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        target="_blank">{GITHUB_REPO_URL}</a
      >.
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>
